.
Hydrating Treatment Essence - this unique blend of extracts and hydrosols can diminish the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, hydrate, and soothe inflammation while addressing UV damage (ingredient list pictured)
.
Routine:

First Aid Beauty Face Cleanser
First Aid Beauty Salicylic Acid Pads (AM: once every few days)
Pixi Hydrating Milky Mist
* @magicmeadowskincare Hydrating Treatment Essence
Pixi Hydrating Milky Lotion (AM)
Paula's Choice Omega+ Complex Moisturizer (PM)
0.025% Tretinoin Cream (PM)
.
I've been struggling with extremely dry skin since starting tret and the owner, Regan, was super helpful in recommending me her Hydrating Treatment Essence, saying that it would be a good extra layer of moisture under my moisturizer.

There were some leaks when I got my package (though I'm told that I'm the only person to report leaky samples), but a little goes a long way and I still had enough of the Essence to apply it once a day for a little over a week. Other than that, I actually really liked the packaging for skincare samples (whereas I hate the reducer tops for perfume). The bottle gives a good amount of product to test over the course of a few days and the orifice reducer helps ensure that you don't go through it too quickly.

The Essence is very smooth, light, and a bit cooling (only a bit -- it's not like rubbing peppermint on your face). The product spreads easily over the skin (I tested application both with and without the Milky Mist underneath and the results were the same) and absorbs quickly (though not too fast that you constantly have to go back for more) with absolutely no greasy feeling.

I tested it for a full week before looking at the product page in an attempt to reduce the risk of forming any biases before writing my review. I remember thinking on the second or third day of testing that my skin felt more plump and smooth after application and being surprised when I checked the product page and read "hydrating", "plumping", and "soothing" in the description. 

